imdb.plot outline: Over 13 stunning episodes we get to know the dedicated and diverse group of Maori professionals and iwi health workers providing services for Maori in and around scenic Whanganui. It's a series full of drama and emotion, set in a region that offers health workers unique challenges - from urbanisation to restricted access into some of New Zealand's most isolated communities.
